title: Scientists find mystery killer whales off Cape Horn, Chile

title_detail.value: Scientists find mystery killer whales off Cape Horn, Chile

summary: In January 2019, scientists working off the tip of southern Chile got their first live look at what might be a new species of killer whale. Genetic samples will help determine whether this animal, with its distinctly different color pattern and body shape, is indeed new to science.
